BENEFITS OF LINEAR REGRESSION MODEL FOR UNDERDEVELOPED COUNTRIES.
Better use of resources: Helps focus limited road safety efforts where they are needed most.
Prevention: Shows what causes serious accidents, so action can be taken to reduce them.
Policy support: Gives evidence to support new rules like speed limits or road repairs.
Low cost: Once built, the model is cheap to run and doesnâ€™t need much data.
Public education: Can be used to teach people about the most dangerous driving conditions.
Road planning: Helps decide which roads or areas need safety improvements.
